This file provides an example of the environment variables needed for LexiSense.

Copy this file to .env and fill in your actual values.

DO NOT commit the .env file to version control.

--- Environment ---

NODE_ENV=development
PORT=3000

--- Security ---

A long, random string used to sign the session ID cookie.
Generate with: openssl rand -base64 32

SESSION_SECRET=your_super_secret_session_key

--- Database ---

The connection string for your PostgreSQL database.
For Neon: Find in your Neon project dashboard
For Render: Use Internal Database URL from Render dashboard

DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:password@host/dbname?sslmode=require

--- AI Service ---

Your API key for the OpenAI service.
Find this in your OpenAI account dashboard.

OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-your_openai_api_key_here

--- File Storage (Required for production) ---

Configure these for your AWS S3 bucket.

S3_BUCKET_NAME=lexisense-contracts
AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=your-aws-access-key
AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=your-aws-secret-key
AWS_REGION=us-east-1

--- Logging (Optional) ---

LOG_LEVEL=info

--- Redis (Optional - for Task #4) ---

REDIS_URL=redis://localhost:6379
